subSubSection.paragraph:
Carapace:
heavily granulated; 1.15‒1.23 (
♂
), 1.09‒1.27 (
♀
) × longer than broad, eyes or eye-spots absent; with 2 deep transverse furrows, posterior furrow closer to posterior margin than anterior furrow; posterior margin of carapace straight; anterior margin with 4 setae (
♂
, 
♀
), posterior margin with 8 (
♂
), 10 (
♀
) setae (
Fig. 3C, F
).

Coxal region:
maxilla smooth except for the antero-lateral region; coxae smooth; manducatory process triangular in shape with 2 apical setae, 1 prolateral suboral seta and 12 (
♂
), 9 (
♀
) additional setae on maxilla. Median max- illary lyrifissure rounded and situated submedially. Chaetotaxy of coxae I‒IV, 
♂
, 9: 9: 8: 15; 
♀
, 10: 13: 11: 20.
